  "description": "Hans Evert Lundström was a district surveyor in Visby. He was born on October 24, 1901, in Sollefteå to engineer Bernhard L. and Hanna Stenbeck. On May 26, 1926, he married Karin Liljefors. They had four children: Hans (born in 1927), Lennart (born in 1930), Lars and Mats (born in 1940). Hans completed his secondary school education in 1920, obtained a surveyor degree in 1926, and a cultural technology degree in 1929. He worked as a surveyor in Malmö County from 1926 to 1928, in Örebro County from 1929 to 1932, in Kristianstad County from 1932 to 1934, and in Södermanland County from 1934 to 1936. From 1936 to 1938, he served as an administrative officer in the surveyor board, and since 1938 he worked as a district surveyor in the Gotland middle district."
